PLAYER: All right!
WOMAN: Get up there!

03:19.106 --> 03:20.386
Six, seven, eight!

03:20.607 --> 03:23.015
Come on, come on.
Climb up. Don't break.

03:23.193 --> 03:24.568
Six, seven, eight.

03:24.735 --> 03:28.355
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight!

03:28.573 --> 03:30.198
Come on, good! Good!

03:30.367 --> 03:32.988
Smile! Look up!
Come on, smile!

03:33.161 --> 03:34.324
There's someone out there!

03:34.496 --> 03:35.775
[SCREAMING]

03:35.954 --> 03:37.235
- There!
CHEERLEADER 1: There!

03:37.414 --> 03:38.445
CHEERLEADER 2:
Where?

03:38.623 --> 03:41.198
CHEERLEADER 3:
I think he's got a gun or something!

03:41.377 --> 03:43.369
CHEERLEADER 2: Pervert!
ALL: Pervert!

03:43.545 --> 03:46.498
Pervert! Pervert! Pervert!

03:46.673 --> 03:48.132
CHEERLEADER 3:
Pervert!

03:49.258 --> 03:52.093
[DOGS BARKING]

03:57.850 --> 04:01.219
[BALL THUDDING]

04:39.264 --> 04:41.470
Could you grab that for me?

04:50.775 --> 04:52.269
Thank you.

04:52.944 --> 04:56.228
- Do you play tennis?
- No. Uh-uh.

04:56.404 --> 05:00.154
- What's that thing?
- A net for insects.

05:00.701 --> 05:02.776
- You collect insects?
- No.

05:02.953 --> 05:05.704
To collect them, you have to kill them.
I just look at them.

05:05.913 --> 05:08.748
Oh. That's nice.

05:11.627 --> 05:13.252
Well, thanks.

05:19.509 --> 05:22.047
["THE NUTCRACKER SUITE" PLAYS]

05:58.587 --> 05:59.619
[MUSIC STOPS]

06:02.549 --> 06:04.458
You're very good.

06:04.634 --> 06:07.505
Not so much when people
are watching me.

06:07.679 --> 06:09.886
- Are you on the team?
- No, I just moved here.

06:10.056 --> 06:11.930
- Is there a team?
- Yeah, at school.

06:12.101 --> 06:14.672
- Which school? Park High?
- Yeah.

06:15.394 --> 06:17.304
You go there?

06:17.939 --> 06:20.062
- You look...
- Younger.

06:20.232 --> 06:24.775
- I'm accelerated.
- Oh, you must be real smart, then.

06:28.114 --> 06:31.199
Well, I'll see you there
when it starts.

06:31.368 --> 06:34.238
- What's your name?
- Maggie.

06:34.705 --> 06:35.984
Hi. I'm Lucas.

06:36.539 --> 06:39.326
- Hi.
- Hi.

06:40.376 --> 06:42.747
- Bye.
- Bye.

06:47.383 --> 06:50.586
LUCAS: All you need to know is
one person. And you already know me.

06:50.761 --> 06:53.216
So when school starts,
you'll have one good friend.

06:53.388 --> 06:55.844
That's all anybody needs
as far as I'm concerned.

06:56.016 --> 06:58.720
Do you think people need
more than just one good friend?

06:58.893 --> 06:59.924
MAGGIE:
Well, yeah.

07:00.103 --> 07:04.147
I'm perfect because I have many
friends. I can introduce you to people.

07:04.315 --> 07:07.980
Hey, guys, what's happening?
Hey, Cappie! How's it hanging, bud?

07:08.152 --> 07:11.069
That's Cappie Foew, number 88.
Good buddy of mine.

07:11.238 --> 07:15.531
There's his girlfriend, Alise,
cheerleading. Been together three years.

07:16.243 --> 07:17.701
You really know those guys?

07:17.869 --> 07:20.443
Do I know those guys?
Of course I know those guys.

07:20.621 --> 07:22.864
I mean, we don't hang out
or anything.

07:23.041 --> 07:26.291
You know, either you're an athlete
or you're not an athlete.

07:26.461 --> 07:28.252
Actually, I am. I'm an athlete.

07:28.421 --> 07:31.706
I don't like to get caught up
in that stuff. It's superficial.

07:31.881 --> 07:34.551
You know, football heroes,
cheerleaders and parties.

07:34.717 --> 07:39.095
I'd be willing to play football if all
that other junk didn't go along with it.

07:39.890 --> 07:41.966
MAGGIE:
My dad's working for this ad agency.

07:42.142 --> 07:43.885
They're doing a blue-jean commercial.

07:44.060 --> 07:46.930
And along comes
Miss Designer Jeans of America...

07:47.104 --> 07:50.973
...who is 19 years old.
And all of a sudden, my dad is like:

07:51.151 --> 07:53.641
"Gosh, I have to work
late again tonight."

07:53.820 --> 07:57.863
And my mom is all, "Gee, he's spending
a lot of time at work lately."

07:58.032 --> 08:01.482
- Well, listen, it happens.
- Not with a girl who's 19.

08:01.660 --> 08:05.575
Age differences can be good.
You have to keep an open mind.

08:05.747 --> 08:08.072
For instance, I'm 14, you're 16.

08:08.249 --> 08:11.499
Could you see me with a man
who's 38 or something?

08:11.669 --> 08:13.662
No. But with a guy of 14...

08:13.838 --> 08:15.878
Would your father
do something like this?

08:16.049 --> 08:18.337
No. Of course he wouldn't.

08:18.509 --> 08:21.082
Well, my father's got
other kinds of problems.

08:21.261 --> 08:22.637
Like what?

08:22.804 --> 08:25.675
Like being a workaholic.
Like being caught in the system.

08:25.849 --> 08:28.056
Both of my parents,
caught in the system.

08:28.227 --> 08:30.218
- Parties and social status.
- That's bad.

08:30.394 --> 08:31.889
- Superficial.
- That's terrible.

08:32.063 --> 08:34.554
That's what I mean about
players and cheerleaders.

08:34.732 --> 08:37.769
- It's all superficial.
- Absolutely.

08:38.068 --> 08:40.856
See? I like the way
you're thinking now.

08:41.030 --> 08:43.236
[CHUCKLES]

08:43.532 --> 08:47.150
- Which one's your house?
- You just passed it.

08:48.287 --> 08:50.742
- That one?
- Yeah.

08:55.293 --> 08:56.704
MAGGIE:
Wow.

08:56.878 --> 09:00.378
LUCAS: See what I mean?
- It's beautiful.

09:00.590 --> 09:05.334
- That materialistic display?
- You don't look like you live there.

09:05.928 --> 09:07.506
That's a compliment.

09:07.680 --> 09:12.721
- Are you a communist?
- No, but I do keep an open mind.

09:12.894 --> 09:15.893
That's what you should do
about things, keep an open mind.

09:16.062 --> 09:19.810
Your father's girlfriend. She might
turn out to be a great mother to you.

09:19.984 --> 09:21.940
She's three years older than me!

09:22.110 --> 09:25.774
LUCAS: Don't get hung up on all
that tradition. Tradition is superficial.

09:25.946 --> 09:29.528
It's just a hang-up.
Haven't you ever realized that?

09:32.828 --> 09:35.699
MAGGIE:
Here's your net.

09:35.998 --> 09:38.120
Here's your umbrella.

09:41.628 --> 09:43.584
Well, bye-bye, Lucas.

09:44.464 --> 09:46.872
It's perfect your name's Maggie.

09:47.176 --> 09:51.089
- Why?
- Because a magpie's black-and-white.

09:52.220 --> 09:53.846
Oh.

09:54.681 --> 09:55.926
Perfect.

09:56.099 --> 09:58.092
[CHUCKLES]

09:59.895 --> 10:02.931
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

10:07.986 --> 10:09.859
[HONKING]

10:28.213 --> 10:29.791
[HONKING]

10:36.262 --> 10:37.672
MAGGIE: Hi!
- Hi!

10:37.846 --> 10:40.718
I've been trying to find you.
I couldn't find this house

10:40.892 --> 10:43.097
- I didn't know your last name.
- Really?

10:43.269 --> 10:46.637
- Yeah. Do you wanna play tennis?
- I wish I could, but I can't.

10:47.271 --> 10:49.727
You have a bug on your shoulder!
Get it off! Quick!

10:49.899 --> 10:51.608
Don't worry.
It's just a locust.

10:51.777 --> 10:54.102
I didn't want to run over it
with the mower.

10:54.279 --> 10:56.686
- Please get it away.
- You should take a look.

10:56.864 --> 11:01.692
You won't see one again for 17 years.
That's how long they take to incubate.

11:02.744 --> 11:05.746
- You can't play tennis?
MAN: Hey, Lucas!

11:06.706 --> 11:09.577
No. I gotta go.
I promised the gardener I'd help him.

11:09.751 --> 11:12.242
- What's your phone number?
- It's unlisted.

11:12.420 --> 11:14.709
And my parents don't like
for me to give it out.

11:14.881 --> 11:15.912
- Oh.
- Yeah.

11:16.091 --> 11:18.878
Well, then maybe
I'll stop by sometime.

11:19.343 --> 11:22.760
They don't like people
to stop by either. I can visit people...

11:22.931 --> 11:26.346
...but they just don't like people
to make a mess of the house and...

11:26.517 --> 11:29.967
- Oh.
- Well, I can meet you there.

11:30.145 --> 11:32.897
- Where?
- The tennis courts by the school.

11:33.065 --> 11:34.345
- When?
- Three o'clock.

11:34.525 --> 11:37.146
- Today?
- Every day!

11:37.319 --> 11:39.027
Okay.

11:40.322 --> 11:42.064
[CHUCKLES]

11:43.032 --> 11:46.483
Lucas. Come on.

11:48.788 --> 11:50.330
Come on!

12:00.090 --> 12:03.292
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

12:19.065 --> 12:21.900
- You're on the wrong side. Keep going!
- I'm compromising.

12:22.069 --> 12:24.857
You don't understand.
Stay on the right side of the road!

12:25.031 --> 12:26.488
Watch where you're going!

12:32.661 --> 12:37.573
- This is creepy, Lucas.
- Don't worry. It's okay.

12:37.750 --> 12:39.576
What if we get lost?

13:16.036 --> 13:19.902
Hi there.
We're with the Chicago Conservatory.

13:20.081 --> 13:21.825
Do you mind if we listen?

13:22.000 --> 13:24.156
- No, fine with me.
- Thank you.

13:25.085 --> 13:29.664
They never mind. Come on, sit down.
Sit over here.

13:31.300 --> 13:34.668
Excuse me.
I hate to bother you again...

13:34.844 --> 13:38.379
...but would you possibly have
a program I could borrow?

13:43.228 --> 13:45.469
Thank you very much.

13:51.443 --> 13:55.358
Whoa. Heavy night!

14:09.627 --> 14:11.251
MAGGIE:
Scootch.

14:27.393 --> 14:30.428
- Maggie?
- Yeah?

14:31.813 --> 14:35.812
- Is your name Margaret?
- Yes.

14:37.152 --> 14:40.652
- Margaret.
- Yeah?

14:40.823 --> 14:42.944
No, I'm just saying it.

14:47.621 --> 14:51.785
Did you think we'd be such
good friends when we first met?

14:52.334 --> 14:54.124
I don't know.

14:56.295 --> 14:58.786
What did you think of me?

15:01.050 --> 15:04.714
I thought you were interesting.

15:06.263 --> 15:08.836
I thought you were beautiful.

15:12.060 --> 15:15.642
- Do you still?
- What?

15:15.980 --> 15:19.847
- Think I'm interesting?
- Yes.

15:21.777 --> 15:23.437
Me too.

15:32.453 --> 15:35.787
Lucas, I think I like classical music.

15:42.463 --> 15:44.006
Lucas?

15:46.258 --> 15:47.717
Yeah?

15:49.260 --> 15:51.669
Is there something wrong?

15:52.473 --> 15:55.758
I just wish that school
would never start.

15:58.437 --> 16:00.558
[BELL RINGING]

16:00.729 --> 16:04.264
MAN 1: Freshmen take the pink form,
sophomores take the gold form...

16:04.442 --> 16:08.605
...juniors take the white form
and the seniors take the yellow form.

16:08.779 --> 16:11.613
WOMAN:
How many trips are we going to take?

16:12.198 --> 16:14.689
I have a sign-up sheet
here for the fall fiesta.

16:14.867 --> 16:17.490
- Because I was all-conference.
- Oh, really?

16:17.704 --> 16:20.160
[CHATTERING]

16:27.462 --> 16:30.797
Excuse me. Making a movie.
Excuse me.

16:31.426 --> 16:34.710
- Blye! Hey, Luca-duke!
- Hey, Ben.

16:34.887 --> 16:37.507
- How was your summer?
- What are you doing?

16:37.681 --> 16:40.635
Fecruiting for the video club.
You want to come out?

16:40.809 --> 16:43.846
- Aren't you going out for band?
- I'm thinking about quitting.

16:44.021 --> 16:45.811
I think maybe you should too.

16:45.980 --> 16:48.767
They say the guy that's
taking over is a real Nazi.

16:48.942 --> 16:51.230
They say he taught band
at Joliet State Prison.

16:51.402 --> 16:53.276
What happened to Triechel?

16:53.446 --> 16:56.197
You didn't hear?
Where have you been?

16:56.365 --> 16:57.776
He's dead.

16:57.950 --> 17:00.655
- What?!
- Yeah. He killed himself.

17:00.828 --> 17:02.736
You didn't know?

17:03.288 --> 17:05.031
GIRL:
Hi, Lucas.

17:05.207 --> 17:08.574
BEN: Oh, hi, Fina.
LUCAS: Hi, Fina.

17:08.751 --> 17:11.502
- How was your summer?
- Did you hear about Triechel?

17:11.671 --> 17:15.087
Yeah, isn't it awful? He blew
a blood vessel playing the trumpet.

17:15.549 --> 17:18.717
- He committed suicide, Fina.
- He did not. He had a stroke.

17:18.886 --> 17:21.376
Are you talking about Triechel?
He blew his head off.

17:21.555 --> 17:24.307
- Playing the trumpet, right?
- Nope. Playing the revolver.

17:24.474 --> 17:27.476
BEN: What did I tell you?
- Jesus!

17:27.644 --> 17:29.352
- Well, why'd he do it?
TONY: Love.

17:29.521 --> 17:31.560
He was in love
with a dental technician.

17:31.731 --> 17:35.514
- She wouldn't give him a shot.
BEN: So he gave himself a shot.

17:35.694 --> 17:38.813
- Triechel?
MAN: Can I have your attention, please?

17:38.988 --> 17:41.195
He didn't seem like the type.

17:41.574 --> 17:43.861
Could you quiet down?

17:44.326 --> 17:46.152
Guys?

17:46.327 --> 17:50.824
I'm tempted to say, "Shut up," here,
but I won't do that.

17:50.999 --> 17:52.743
Want to go to the movies tonight?

17:52.918 --> 17:56.962
You've all been real cooperative today.
I know it's been kind of confusing...

17:57.130 --> 18:01.708
...and crazed and congested,
and we're running 90 minutes late.

18:01.885 --> 18:06.095
So we're going to postpone
registration until Monday.

18:06.304 --> 18:07.336
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

18:07.514 --> 18:12.010
And if you'll all now proceed
in an orderly fashion to the gym.

18:12.436 --> 18:14.808
I said, in an orderly fashion!

18:14.980 --> 18:19.273
We're going to have a short program
that I'm sure you're all gonna enjoy.

18:19.443 --> 18:22.111
Pirates can't be beat!

18:22.279 --> 18:26.275
[CHANTING CHEER]

18:43.965 --> 18:46.503
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

18:53.265 --> 18:57.014
I wanna introduce you
to the Pirates right now.

18:58.354 --> 19:02.185
You know them by name,
you know them by number!

19:13.409 --> 19:16.445
Let's get them up here.
Come on up, now!

19:16.995 --> 19:21.040
- Come right on up! Come on.
- All right!

19:21.208 --> 19:23.745
COACH:
Up here on the stage.

19:23.918 --> 19:27.370
- Come on, boys. Hustle it up!
- Way to go!

19:27.797 --> 19:30.039
Hey, Luke!
What are you, the football?

19:30.216 --> 19:33.253
COACH:
Let's let everybody see your faces.

19:33.428 --> 19:38.089
These are the men whose names
are gonna spell victory!

19:38.265 --> 19:40.673
Hey! Look who's going out
for the football team!

19:40.851 --> 19:43.520
Leukoplakia!
Come on up, Luke.

19:43.687 --> 19:47.731
- Come on! The stage is this way!
COACH: Come on, Bruno.

19:51.069 --> 19:56.775
Let's go, Luke! Let's go, Luke!
Let's go, Luke! Let's go, Luke!

19:56.950 --> 20:00.484
Hey, Cappie! Your buddy's
coming out for the team!

20:03.289 --> 20:06.206
[STUDENTS CHANTING
AND SCREAMING]

20:06.375 --> 20:08.617
Hey, Bruno! Hey, let him go!

20:11.129 --> 20:14.463
- All right.
COACH: Okay.

20:21.847 --> 20:24.764
- All right!
- I'd like to get on with this, please.

20:29.063 --> 20:31.387
Whoa! Whoa!

20:31.564 --> 20:33.142
Okay.

20:34.484 --> 20:37.188
PLAYER: All right.
COACH: That's enough, you guys.

20:42.534 --> 20:43.565
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

20:44.326 --> 20:46.284
All right, if we can...

20:46.454 --> 20:48.410
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

20:49.373 --> 20:52.540
If we can get serious, here...

20:54.962 --> 20:59.291
...I wanna introduce the men
who really belong on this stage.

21:06.306 --> 21:08.511
Okay. All right.

21:09.683 --> 21:11.890
Can you get off the stage, son?

21:16.689 --> 21:20.984
Will you get off the stage?
Fight over there.

21:41.671 --> 21:43.629
All right. Captain of the team...

21:43.799 --> 21:47.631
...that's gonna beat Rockford
in our first game in two weeks...

21:47.803 --> 21:52.095
...I want to introduce to you now
number 88, Cappie Foew!

21:52.264 --> 21:53.545
All right!

22:02.107 --> 22:03.684
MAGGIE:
Lucas!

22:04.359 --> 22:06.019
Lucas!

22:07.279 --> 22:08.737
Yeah, hi.

22:08.905 --> 22:12.738
- Are you all right?
- Me? Yeah. Were you in there?

22:12.910 --> 22:16.028
That was funny, wasn't it?
That was planned.

22:19.206 --> 22:20.950
Well, see you.

22:22.251 --> 22:24.788
What are you doing this weekend?

22:25.421 --> 22:29.418
- I don't know. What are you doing?
- My dad's visiting.

22:29.591 --> 22:31.085
Great.

22:31.468 --> 22:36.842
- I hope he doesn't bring his girlfriend.
- Well, remember, keep an open mind.

22:37.682 --> 22:42.759
Lucas, are your parents going
to this parents' night thing?

22:42.937 --> 22:46.638
I thought maybe we could
introduce them to my mom...

22:46.816 --> 22:49.354
...because she doesn't know anybody.

22:49.652 --> 22:51.110
No.

22:51.278 --> 22:53.650
- No?
- No, they don't do that!

22:53.822 --> 22:55.103
Oh.

22:55.282 --> 23:00.358
Well, I thought I told you!
They're superficial. Well, didn't I?

23:00.995 --> 23:04.115
- Yes, Lucas.
- Okay, then.

23:06.168 --> 23:09.453
You know who else you told me
was superficial?

23:09.794 --> 23:11.288
Who?

23:12.089 --> 23:14.128
Football players.

23:16.677 --> 23:21.671
You were right too. They think
you're someone to make fun of.

23:25.434 --> 23:31.271
Uh, listen, I heard they're playing
something funny at the movies tonight.

23:37.863 --> 23:39.487
Come here.

23:53.962 --> 23:56.416
[CHATTERING]

23:59.633 --> 24:01.791
The movie's about to start.
Let's go!

24:05.639 --> 24:09.173
Hey, Blye! You want me
to get your tickets?

24:09.851 --> 24:12.805
[HONKING]

24:17.316 --> 24:21.777
BRUNO: Hey, Luke, Luke, Luke, Luke
Get that ball away and puke

24:21.946 --> 24:26.026
If you need to go in front of my car,
go ahead. Really, I won't kill you.

24:26.200 --> 24:28.525
I cross my heart.
Seriously, go ahead.

24:34.041 --> 24:36.116
[HONKING]

24:37.002 --> 24:38.460
CAPPIE: Hey, Luke.
LUCAS: Hi.

24:38.628 --> 24:40.584
- How was your summer?
LUCAS: It was good.

24:40.755 --> 24:42.628
- All right.
- You were a good sport today.

24:42.839 --> 24:44.499
Thanks.

24:44.674 --> 24:46.834
- Hi.
- Hi. This is Maggie, guys.

24:47.011 --> 24:48.837
- Hi.
- Hello.

24:49.013 --> 24:51.301
- I got our tickets. Got our tickets.
- Thank you.

24:51.472 --> 24:54.142
CAPPIE: We'll see you inside, okay?
SPIKE: Bye, Luke.

24:54.308 --> 24:56.432
TONTO: Bye, Lucas.
- Sorry I'm late.

25:00.774 --> 25:03.560
Hey, Luke! You want something?

25:09.656 --> 25:11.815
- Thanks.
SALESGIRL: Sure. Can I help you?

25:11.992 --> 25:15.942
Yes, ma'am. I'd like
a tub of popcorn with butter...

25:16.121 --> 25:19.536
...a large Coke, a small Coke
and, since I'm on a diet...

25:19.707 --> 25:22.329
...I'll have either Goobers or M&M's.
Which one, guys?

25:22.502 --> 25:23.533
M&M's.

25:23.711 --> 25:27.661
Luke, Luke, Luke, Luke
Get that ball away and puke

25:27.840 --> 25:30.248
Ben and Luke
I'm gonna puke

25:31.594 --> 25:33.254
- What a gimp.
- Come on, let's go.

25:33.429 --> 25:36.713
- Hey! Don't let him scare you away.
- Scare me away?

25:36.889 --> 25:38.930
Yeah. Just tell him to eat shit.

25:39.101 --> 25:42.469
Yeah, I'd like some Feese's Pieces,
some Milk Duds...

25:42.645 --> 25:46.394
...and some red twisty things
for my girlfriend, please.

25:46.566 --> 25:49.021
So! What do you guys say?

25:49.193 --> 25:51.649
You coming out
for the football team or not?

25:51.821 --> 25:56.946
We're trying to find you a jersey,
but we're all out of pup tents.

25:57.118 --> 25:59.442
You should talk, shit-breath.

25:59.619 --> 26:01.695
- What did you say?
- You heard me.

26:01.871 --> 26:03.330
No, I don't think I did.

26:03.498 --> 26:05.990
- What's going on?
- This kid's mouthing off to me.

26:06.168 --> 26:07.331
- Let's go.
- Wait a second.

26:07.502 --> 26:09.329
- What's the point?
- I'm kidding around.

26:09.504 --> 26:12.124
And this fat little marshmallow
opens his mouth to me.

26:12.297 --> 26:14.207
Don't worry about him.
Let's see a movie.

26:14.383 --> 26:17.634
You better watch your mouth, fat boy.
Learn to be like Lucas.

26:17.804 --> 26:22.298
- He's smart. Not like you.
- He's scared. Not like me.

26:22.724 --> 26:25.049
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

26:25.477 --> 26:28.810
- You know, you're asking for it.
- Well, so are you!

26:28.980 --> 26:31.353
- What did you say?
- You heard me!

26:31.525 --> 26:33.731
Maybe you boys would like
to step outside.

26:33.902 --> 26:35.941
ANGIE: Let's go.
- No, I have to settle this.

26:36.111 --> 26:38.105
- I came to see a movie.
- And so did I.

26:38.281 --> 26:40.772
- Yeah, but not King Kong.
- Hey, man!

26:40.950 --> 26:44.035
CAPPIE: Settle down.
- Let's go. No fights! I mean it!

26:44.203 --> 26:45.697
You should listen to the lady.

26:45.871 --> 26:48.871
If I was you, I wouldn't stick around
to see the movie.

26:49.040 --> 26:53.203
You understand me, Leukoplakia?
I'll be looking for you guys afterwards.

26:53.378 --> 26:54.956
- No, he won't.
- The hell I won't.

26:55.130 --> 26:56.790
- They'll be with me afterwards.
- Yeah?

26:56.965 --> 26:57.996
We're going out to eat.

26:58.174 --> 27:01.625
- Why do you always stick up for him?
- Why are you always picking on him?

27:01.802 --> 27:03.594
ANGIE:
Let's go. The movie's started.

27:03.763 --> 27:06.928
Just make sure we're on
opposite sides of the line tomorrow.

27:07.098 --> 27:08.640
Sure.

27:12.271 --> 27:13.730
Can I get a Feese's, please?

27:13.897 --> 27:15.439
- Do you want anything?
ALISE: No.

27:15.607 --> 27:18.441
- Maybe we should leave.
- I'm not afraid of that shit-bag.

27:18.818 --> 27:23.315
- Don't worry about it. We're going out.
- I can't. My mom's picking me up.

27:23.490 --> 27:25.814
- Sorry about that.
- Yeah, well, so am I.

27:25.992 --> 27:27.321
I'll see you guys inside.

27:28.202 --> 27:32.199
I didn 't believe it. But you saw it.
You saw it, didn 't you?

27:32.372 --> 27:35.373
Yes, I... I saw it.
I thought she was...

27:35.877 --> 27:39.327
ACTOF:
As God is my witness, I saw the thing.

27:39.505 --> 27:43.169
PFICE: You've committed murder
just as much as Elaine did.

27:43.341 --> 27:46.211
MAGGIE:
Why do they call you Leukoplakia?

27:49.722 --> 27:52.047
Does it mean something?

27:54.976 --> 27:58.393
Leukoplakia is cancer of the mouth.

28:16.706 --> 28:18.579
I think they've done it.

28:20.500 --> 28:25.839
It's the same with pigeons.
You can tell by the way they kiss.

28:37.182 --> 28:40.052
Help me! Help me!

28:41.062 --> 28:42.521
[SCREAMING]

28:42.938 --> 28:44.563
[MUSIC PLAYS]

28:44.731 --> 28:46.855
[CHATTERING]

28:52.321 --> 28:56.901
It was huge, man! Huge! "Help me!
Help me! Help me! Help me!"

28:57.327 --> 28:58.572
Let's score some beers.

28:58.745 --> 29:00.986
TONTO:
Screw beers. Let's get bandoleros!

29:01.246 --> 29:03.120
- What are bandoleros?
- I don't know.

29:03.289 --> 29:05.827
But some guy said he'd get
great bandoleros.

29:06.000 --> 29:09.205
- Can we get a little organization here?
MARY ELLEN: Let's turn it up.

29:09.380 --> 29:14.041
SPIKE: It's a great song.
MARIE: Come on, turn it up! All right!

29:24.769 --> 29:27.888
- What was that?
CAPPIE: Jesus!

29:28.105 --> 29:29.812
[SCREAMING]

29:40.492 --> 29:42.567
TONTO: Jesus Christ!
MARY ELLEN: What was that?

29:42.743 --> 29:45.068
- Is everybody all right?
SPIKE: I don't believe it!

29:45.245 --> 29:47.239
- Holy shit!
MARY ELLEN: Are you okay?

29:47.415 --> 29:50.167
CAPPIE: Are you all right?
MARIE: I thought I was gonna die!

29:50.334 --> 29:53.039
"Help me! Help me! Help me!"

29:53.295 --> 29:55.169
TONTO:
You think the car's all right?

29:55.338 --> 29:58.754
SPIKE: Let's take a look at the hood.
TONTO: Let's check it out.

29:59.467 --> 30:03.216
- You all right?
- Yeah. Look at the windshield.

30:05.098 --> 30:08.014
- What were those things?
MARIE: I don't know, they were scary!

30:08.183 --> 30:12.312
TONTO: Something hit me in the face.
ALISE: They were bugs.

30:12.689 --> 30:15.013
It was locusts. Listen!

30:15.190 --> 30:18.441
MARIE: To what?
MARY ELLEN: I can't hear anything.

30:18.611 --> 30:22.477
CAPPIE: I don't hear anything.
- They're hatching in the trees.

30:24.074 --> 30:27.360
- I wanna get out of here.
- They can't hurt you.

30:27.536 --> 30:30.027
I don't care.
I want to get out of here.

30:30.204 --> 30:33.704
- In Africa, people eat them.
SPIKE: Get the mustard.

30:33.874 --> 30:35.748
- I wanna get out of here.
CAPPIE: Felax.

30:35.918 --> 30:37.826
I just wanna get out of here!

30:38.003 --> 30:40.625
I hate to say this,
but there's something in your hair.

30:40.799 --> 30:43.086
- Shut up!
- I'm serious!

30:43.967 --> 30:47.087
ALISE: Oh, shit!
CAPPIE: Alise. Alise, relax. Felax!

30:47.262 --> 30:50.132
It's okay! It's all right!
Settle down.

30:50.306 --> 30:53.473
I'll get it! I'll get it!
Calm down. Look, I got it.

30:53.643 --> 30:58.055
CAPPIE: Did you get it?
- I got it. Look, it's out. It's out.

30:58.731 --> 31:00.688
- It's okay.
MAGGIE: See?

31:00.858 --> 31:01.937
CAPPIE:
It's just a bug.

31:02.109 --> 31:04.184
[LOCUST CHIFPING]

31:04.360 --> 31:07.730
- Thank you.
- I don't mind them.

31:07.990 --> 31:12.070
- Lucas told me all about them.
LUCAS: You got one? Let me see it.

31:12.285 --> 31:14.823
TONTO: Let's see.
SPIKE: Is that thing for real?

31:14.996 --> 31:17.153
TONTO: Check it out.
- All right!

31:17.330 --> 31:19.455
SPIKE: Into the light.
TONTO: I can't see it.

31:19.625 --> 31:22.958
MARIE: Look how big it is!
- I gotta be real delicate. It's a baby.

31:23.129 --> 31:27.671
It's the first time it's seen the world.
It just hatched.

31:27.841 --> 31:31.424
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Are there any more in my hair?

31:31.846 --> 31:33.174
No, I don't see any.

31:35.182 --> 31:36.724
ALL:
Wow.

31:36.891 --> 31:39.049
MARIE: Look at its wings!
TONTO: Check it out!

31:39.226 --> 31:41.183
MARIE: Look at that!
TONTO: It doesn't move.

31:41.353 --> 31:45.019
MARY ELLEN: It's not trying to get away.
SPIKE: Hey, it must be dumb.

31:45.191 --> 31:48.809
It's not dumb. Its wings are still wet.
It's totally helpless.

31:48.987 --> 31:50.894
SPIKE:
I've never seen these things before.

31:51.070 --> 31:53.110
LUCAS:
They only hatch out every 17 years.

31:53.281 --> 31:55.819
MARY ELLEN: How come every 17 years?
- He loves bugs.

31:55.992 --> 31:58.234
He's a great kid.

31:59.704 --> 32:04.330
- Thanks for sticking up for him.
- It's okay. I like him.

32:04.500 --> 32:06.327
I'm glad.

32:06.585 --> 32:11.213
- He did something for me once.
MAGGIE: Did he? Well, what did he do?

32:11.383 --> 32:15.213
Cappie? Can we get
out of here right now?

32:15.386 --> 32:17.425
- Please?
- Sure.

32:21.141 --> 32:24.640
MARY ELLEN: I think it's ugly.
MARIE: Does it bite?

32:24.811 --> 32:27.562
LUCAS: It doesn't have a mouth.
All it lives for is to mate.

32:27.730 --> 32:31.810
TONTO: Hey, like me!
- I think it's moving a little.

32:31.984 --> 32:34.392
LUCAS: What are you doing?
TONTO: Step on it!

32:34.569 --> 32:36.859
- Don't!
MARIE: Guys! I got it!

32:37.031 --> 32:40.197
Oh, my God, it looks like a huge M&M!

32:41.118 --> 32:44.949
SPIKE: That's disgusting.
Let's get out of here. Let's go.

32:47.122 --> 32:48.154
[CAR STARTS]

32:48.332 --> 32:50.741
CAPPIE:
Hey, guys, come on, let's go.

32:51.878 --> 32:54.582
- Luke!
ALISE: Let's go.

32:57.048 --> 32:58.626
CAPPIE:
Luke, come on.

33:08.851 --> 33:11.140
[BAND PLAYS MAFCHING MUSIC]

33:30.790 --> 33:34.738
WOMAN: And I always like a big, strong,
handsome man in the kitchen with me.

33:34.918 --> 33:36.625
Because a big, strong man...

33:36.794 --> 33:40.957
...always seems to feel so helpless.

33:41.132 --> 33:44.002
- Well, you don't seem very helpless.
- No, ma'am.

33:44.176 --> 33:46.927
- You've broken a banana very well.
- Thank you.

33:47.095 --> 33:48.923
Something handed down
from my ancestors.

33:49.139 --> 33:52.140
TEACHEF:
By the family tree, you might say?

33:52.309 --> 33:53.636
You might say, yeah.

33:54.311 --> 33:56.931
TEACHEF: Ready to make your drink?
CAPPIE: Yeah.

33:57.105 --> 34:00.106
- Are you capable of handling this?
- Quite capable, yes.

34:00.275 --> 34:02.813
I mean, you've never
used a blender before.

34:02.986 --> 34:05.606
- No problem.
- Anything you've left out?

34:05.779 --> 34:08.187
Bananas, milk.
Not that I can see, no.

34:08.366 --> 34:12.493
- Nothing that you, overlooked?
- No, ma'am.

34:12.828 --> 34:15.782
All right, then. Blend away.

34:19.333 --> 34:21.327
TONTO:
Way to go, sport!

34:21.585 --> 34:25.666
Who'd like to show this big, strong
man how to use the washer-dryer?

34:29.677 --> 34:33.127
MAGGIE: I think there's a gizmo
to put this in...

34:33.347 --> 34:36.134
...but I just sprinkle it on top.

34:37.434 --> 34:40.850
Okay. Oh, mini-cycle.

34:41.021 --> 34:44.306
- And that's that.
- Okay.

34:44.649 --> 34:46.607
So...

34:46.985 --> 34:51.231
- I hope it gets done in time.
- So do I. Yeah.

34:51.405 --> 34:53.612
Uh... Do you wanna go or?

34:53.783 --> 34:57.068
Oh, well, you know how
to use the dryer?

34:57.244 --> 35:00.162
Yeah, I think I can do it.
I just don't know where to start.

35:00.331 --> 35:03.664
- I have 15 minutes.
- Okay.

35:11.590 --> 35:13.879
Table for two? Care to join me?

35:14.051 --> 35:15.759
[MAGGIE GIGGLING]

35:23.143 --> 35:26.180
- Very boring.
- Very.

35:26.897 --> 35:29.055
I guarantee the dryer
will be a lot worse.

35:29.233 --> 35:30.312
[GIGGLING]

35:30.484 --> 35:32.523
[WASHEF BANGING]

35:32.694 --> 35:35.777
Don't panic. It's trying to get out.

35:36.530 --> 35:38.773
[WASHEF STOPS BANGING]

35:41.285 --> 35:43.408
Pretty good.

35:58.300 --> 36:00.174
[PAPEF FUSTLING]

36:03.597 --> 36:04.973
Some gum?

36:07.810 --> 36:09.184
It's good for you.

36:09.352 --> 36:11.760
- Really?
- Oh, yeah. Dextrose, softeners...

36:11.938 --> 36:14.773
...artificial flavors. Good stuff.

36:29.329 --> 36:31.537
I like Alise.

36:31.998 --> 36:33.826
She's real pretty.

36:34.001 --> 36:35.827
Thanks.

36:36.127 --> 36:39.081
You guys been going together
a long time?

36:39.339 --> 36:41.083
Yeah.

36:42.258 --> 36:44.630
It's real serious, huh?

36:46.345 --> 36:48.634
Well, it's serious, but...

36:50.474 --> 36:52.016
I don't know about this gum.

36:52.352 --> 36:55.636
I didn't wanna say anything. Here.

36:58.815 --> 37:01.389
Some people would
be grossed out by that.

37:01.568 --> 37:04.273
- Not me.
- I know Alise would.

37:04.446 --> 37:08.193
- She gets easily grossed out.
- I don't.

37:08.365 --> 37:11.237
Well, except for some things.

37:11.411 --> 37:13.902
Some things? Like?

37:14.080 --> 37:15.740
Like...

37:16.957 --> 37:19.957
- Like what?
- Like phlegm or something...

37:20.126 --> 37:22.368
...when it flies out of a handkerchief.

37:22.545 --> 37:26.959
Or if someone throws up on your shoe.
You know, that happened to me once.

37:27.217 --> 37:31.676
- Well, you asked.
- No, tell me about it. I'm interested.

37:31.846 --> 37:36.224
We were on this plane to Orlando,
I was wearing Loafers and no socks.

37:36.393 --> 37:41.349
And I have two hours left on this flight
when this man threw up on my shoe.

37:41.605 --> 37:45.056
It was really disgusting.

37:57.370 --> 37:59.942
- How was Orlando?
- Oh, it was fantastic.

38:00.123 --> 38:03.491
- I'm gonna travel myself someday.
- Oh, me too.

38:08.171 --> 38:10.627
What's up with you and Lucas?
I mean, as far as...

38:10.799 --> 38:13.752
- We're just friends.
- Yeah?

38:14.135 --> 38:16.626
He's very special.

38:16.804 --> 38:20.138
- Oh, he's the best.
- And he's so smart.

38:20.308 --> 38:23.309
- You're telling me how smart he is?
- You know...

38:23.477 --> 38:27.426
...it's nice to know somebody
who has really heavy thoughts.

38:27.605 --> 38:29.813
- Absolutely. Yeah.
- Do you?

38:31.194 --> 38:33.981
- What?
- Have heavy thoughts?

38:34.155 --> 38:37.569
Oh, yeah, sure. All the time.

38:39.283 --> 38:41.573
I'm not having any right now...

38:42.286 --> 38:44.659
...but just give me some time.

38:56.383 --> 38:58.589
What did he do for you?

38:59.886 --> 39:04.880
- You said he helped you once.
- Oh, right. Yeah, with my schoolwork.

39:05.058 --> 39:08.059
I was out with this case of hepatitis
for a couple months...

39:08.228 --> 39:11.845
...and he came by my house every day
and brought my books to me.

39:12.023 --> 39:14.560
I still don't know why he did it.

39:15.859 --> 39:18.267
Because you're nice to him.

39:24.409 --> 39:26.567
I didn't used to be.

39:32.250 --> 39:35.167
I used to treat him
like everybody else does.

39:36.545 --> 39:38.253
Why do people do that?

39:38.630 --> 39:42.331
I don't know.
Because he's strange, I guess.

39:42.801 --> 39:45.587
You know, last year he even had
this strange walk.

39:45.761 --> 39:49.890
He said it had something to do
with the force of gravity.

39:50.850 --> 39:53.886
Just the way he mouths off
in class sometimes.

39:54.062 --> 39:56.101
That's how the term
"Leukoplakia" got started.

39:56.271 --> 39:57.552
Oh.

39:59.775 --> 40:02.444
Anyways, I do owe a lot to him.

40:03.071 --> 40:04.730
And I like him.

40:05.406 --> 40:07.314
I do too.

40:09.158 --> 40:12.575
So I'll do what I can
to keep him from getting hurt.

40:13.497 --> 40:15.288
Yeah.

40:16.875 --> 40:18.618
And then there's Alise.

40:19.459 --> 40:21.287
- Fight.
- I mean, she likes him too.

40:21.462 --> 40:23.039
Oh, right.

40:23.213 --> 40:25.289
That's nice.

40:26.885 --> 40:29.374
She thinks you're very beautiful.

40:29.552 --> 40:31.924
- Really?
- Yeah.

40:33.014 --> 40:35.255
Did she say that?

40:36.642 --> 40:38.850
I think she's jealous.

40:39.021 --> 40:41.724
Of me? Why?

40:48.571 --> 40:50.444
Are you cold?

41:22.853 --> 41:25.059
Oh, no!

41:25.230 --> 41:27.102
CAPPIE:
He shoots! He scores!

41:28.315 --> 41:32.100
Whoa! What a shot!
Look out! This kid's an all-American!

41:32.278 --> 41:34.401
What a shot!

41:34.906 --> 41:38.356
Tied now. No time left. Pulls up.

41:38.533 --> 41:40.443
Money shot!

41:40.619 --> 41:41.817
[MAGGIE GIGGLING]

41:43.705 --> 41:46.659
I told Alise I thought you should
try out for cheerleading.

41:46.917 --> 41:49.371
That's why she got jealous.

41:49.835 --> 41:52.124
I still think you should.

41:52.629 --> 41:54.872
[BELL RINGING]

42:13.399 --> 42:15.772
ALISE: So it's an honor
to represent the school.

42:15.944 --> 42:19.478
And it looks real good on college
applications. And anybody can join.

42:19.655 --> 42:22.941
Even boys. The Supreme Court
says anyone who tries out for a team...

42:23.117 --> 42:25.904
...has to be given a chance.
GIRL 1: I'd like to point out...

42:26.078 --> 42:28.616
...that cheerleading is
very good exercise for your body.

42:28.789 --> 42:31.280
A lot of doctors say
it's even better than aerobics.

42:31.458 --> 42:34.872
GIRL 2: And it's not too bad
for your social life either.

42:35.043 --> 42:38.295
- What's going on here?
- Shh.

42:38.465 --> 42:42.165
- What are you doing here?
- I'm listening.

42:42.343 --> 42:45.129
Can you meet me after school?
I'll get you an A in biology.

42:45.304 --> 42:48.802
- Shh.
ALISE: We have eight places to fill.

42:48.973 --> 42:52.474
We practice every day and take buses
with the guys to the away games.

42:52.645 --> 42:56.142
Some bus drivers don't care
what goes on in the back of the bus.

42:56.313 --> 42:58.851
Or what beverages may be consumed.

42:59.108 --> 43:01.895
- Don't say you heard it here.
ALISE: If anyone's interested...

43:02.070 --> 43:06.566
...take an application and meet at
the practice field right after school today.

43:16.751 --> 43:19.205
- You have a change of clothes here?
- Why?

43:19.377 --> 43:23.042
If you come down to the stream and
collect stuff for Karlson's terrarium...

43:23.214 --> 43:25.041
...I'm sure he'll give you an A.

43:26.008 --> 43:27.752
Maggie?

43:28.261 --> 43:30.930
- When?
- Today.

43:31.138 --> 43:33.759
I think I'm gonna do this today.

43:34.516 --> 43:36.177
Cheerleading?

43:36.352 --> 43:39.269
- Well, check it out.
- What for?

43:39.438 --> 43:42.522
- Because I might wanna do it.
- What, be a cheerleader?

43:42.690 --> 43:44.600
I don't know.

43:44.776 --> 43:47.563
- Is that all right, Lucas?
- Me? Hey...

43:47.737 --> 43:51.319
- The way you were looking at me...
- Whatever.

43:51.490 --> 43:54.611
I can wait till tomorrow
to collect tadpoles.

43:55.161 --> 43:58.529
Well, if I like it, I'll be
doing it tomorrow too.

43:58.706 --> 44:01.113
They practice every day.

44:03.169 --> 44:06.453
It sounds like fun, Lucas.

44:08.339 --> 44:12.289
Well, didn't you hear what they said?
Away games and buses...

44:12.677 --> 44:14.634
...and stuff.

44:14.804 --> 44:18.421
Well, I guess everybody
has their own idea of fun.

44:19.307 --> 44:21.930
Some people go to football games.

44:22.103 --> 44:25.721
Other people do
less superficial things.

44:25.898 --> 44:28.768
Look, Lucas, just because
you don't approve of something...

44:28.942 --> 44:33.355
...doesn't mean other people
don't have a right to enjoy it.

44:33.530 --> 44:36.614
- Well, you're in the band, aren't you?
- Yeah.

44:36.783 --> 44:37.813
- So?
- So?

44:38.033 --> 44:41.533
- So the band goes to football games.
- Well, totally different.

44:41.703 --> 44:44.277
- Why?
- The band does not have fun there.

44:44.456 --> 44:46.948
- Then why do you do it?
- Well, I don't know.

44:47.126 --> 44:50.825
Figure it out. And in the meantime,
don't call people superficial...

44:51.004 --> 44:52.961
...just because they wanna have fun!

44:54.382 --> 44:56.006
I'm new here.

44:56.175 --> 44:59.046
I don't know anybody.

44:59.220 --> 45:04.012
Why can't you be helpful
and understanding about that?

45:13.734 --> 45:16.022
[CHANTING]

46:02.653 --> 46:04.563
BOY:
Hey, Laura, wait up.

46:06.742 --> 46:11.070
Hi. Hey, thanks for waiting for me.
I've gotta talk to you.

46:11.245 --> 46:14.696
I thought about what you said to me,
